June 17 at 12:46 PM ·

Tonight we will be honoring the class of 2020 of the Hitchcock/Tulare High School at 7:00 pm with a Baccalaureate service at the Hitchcock United Methodist Church. We will be doing Facebook live on the church Facebook page and the school will be live streaming to their cable TV channel, we have asked that only the graduates and immediate family attend in person. Mask use is at the comfort and discretion of the individual, we will ask all to physically distance by family groups. Please join us in wishing our Senior class of 2020 God's rich blessings on their future plans.

post_text:
Hitchcock-Tulare 2020 Graduation Ceremony

When: Saturday, June 20th at 2:00 PM

Where: Tulare Football Field

Bleacher seating and a limited number of chairs will be available so please bring your lawn chairs or a blanket and join us for this outdoor graduation ceremony.

Due to a lack of internet connectivity at the football field the graduation ceremony will be recorded in its entirety and posted to the Hitchcock-Tulare YouTube channel, Facebook page, and on Venture Channel 384 at 3:00 PM on Saturday, June 20th following the actual ceremony.

On behalf of the graduates, please join them after the ceremony to celebrate at their respective locations. Details from their announcements will be followed for individual receptions so please refer to each graduates announcement.

Senior Spotlight - Logan Gilbert
I plan to attend Lake Area Technical Institute for precision Ag.
My Favorite High-school memory was beating Wolsey in basketball two years ago and winning homecoming football game this year.
My favorite activity in school was playing football the relationship I built with everyone through this will last forever.
My favorite class was all my AG classes with Mr. Brink his classes were always fun and we always learned something new. He always pushed us to be the best we could be in anything we would do.
And during this quarantine it has actually made me miss school for once in my life just seeing all my friends everyday would be nice have again.

Spink Conservation District
April 24 at 9:36 AM ·

HAPPY ARBOR DAY!!! We would like to congratulate Lila Johnson of Frankfort on winning the state Arbor Day Essay contest. Her essay is below...

Old branches sway down by the river. My favorite tree on the farm is home to eagles. On our farm, we call it the Bald Eagle Tree. The tree has been through a lot from fires, floods, drought, and many more. It has also watched my farm grow from small to big. The tree has stood tall and strong for a long time. The eagles have a huge nest to have their young. Every year, the eagles fly away but they always come back. The baby and its parents will fly around while we plant our fields. The tree watches the eagles fly. If a storm comes, the tree will protect them. If the tree were to die, everyone would be sad. But the tree protects them through it all. That's why I think people should plant trees. Trees are very important.

Let’s have a little fun!!! With Easter right around the corner and the kids not being able to get out and participate in normal Easter activities and homeschooling in full effect. We thought we could add a little fun to both. We decided to do a Virtual Easter Egg Hunt. All you have to do is choose a photo of an Easter Egg from the site listed below have your child/children color it and take a picture of the photo and upload it to this page. The one with the most “likes” in each age group: Preschool,Kindegarten, 1st-3rd, 4th-6th will win an Easter Basket. Have Fun and Happy Coloring!!

Good morning! I hope this email finds you all healthy and well. I know with everything going on right now that life can seem a little overwhelming and uncertainty of what tomorrow holds can create fear and anxiety. I hope you all know the Hitchcock-Tulare School District is committed to our staff and students and will do everything possible to provide a valuable and relevant education for our students while still addressing the safety and well-being of our staff and students during these trying times. At this time, there is a lot of uncertainty across our state with what tomorrow or next week holds. I will provide information and details as they become available to me as well as plans for Hitchcock-Tulare School as they are made. As this virus spreads across our state and region please be safe and do your part to help stop the spread.

post_text: Good evening everyone. We hope you are all staying safe and appreciate all of your efforts and support as we navigate through this new and challenging situation. I wanted to take a couple of minutes and update you on a couple of things. All evening and extra-curricular activities for the Hitchcock-Tulare School District have been postponed or cancelled through April 5th. This does include Prom which we are working to get rescheduled. We also want people to know that once we return back to normal school we will be a 5 day week until school is out. We would still observe Good Friday as a day off but would be in school Easter Monday and all enhancement days would be full school days. Once again please stay safe and thank you for your understanding.

post_text: The Hitchcock-Tulare School District will honor the Governor’s directive for all schools to close next week across the state of South Dakota and be close Monday, March 16th through Thursday, March 19th. All Hitchcock-Tulare School buildings will be closed to everyone until further notice outside of essential custodial or administrative staff. Our buildings have been cleaned and disinfected and we want them to stay that way until we re-open. We will be in contact with state agencies and pass along necessary information as it becomes available. Please be safe and take any necessary precautions to avoid contact and spread of this disease. High school students who are in Chemistry or Spanish need to check their email daily to stay up to date on assignments as instruction for these courses will continue. When we re-open we will be reminding everyone that is sick or has a fever to stay home until they are fever free for 24 hrs without Tylenol or Ibuprofen. Thank you.
